This paper discusses the benefits of population diversity in evolutionary algorithms, which are commonly used in the field of computational intelligence and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of diversity in multiobjective optimization, which falls under the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the effectiveness of crossover and mutation, which are common techniques in machine learning and optimization, and thus could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the importance of diversity in dynamic optimization, which could be categorized under cs.SE (Software Engineering).
